  "title": "Supply Chain Support (Fresh welcome)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the supply chain team with daily operations and administrative tasks.</li><li>Support order processing, including receiving, entering, and tracking orders in the system.</li><li>Assist with inventory management, reconcile stock records, and prepare inventory reports</li><li>Liaise with suppliers and logistics partners to follow up on shipments and delivery schedules</li><li>Prepare and maintain supply chain documents and records to ensure accuracy.</li><li>Support cross-department communication with Procurement, Warehouse, Logistics, and Finance.</li><li>Assist in generating regular reports and presentations for the supply chain team.</li><li>Perform other ad hoc tasks assigned by supervisors.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>• Degree/Diploma in Purchasing, Logistics, Materials Management, Procurement, International Supply Chain Management, or equivalent.<br />• Strong team player with excellent communication and interpersonal skills.<br />• Independent, reliable, and analytical.<br /><strong>• Fresh graduates are welcome to apply!</strong><br /><br />EA License No: 95C2823</p><p>EA Personnel No: R23112241</p><p>EA Personnel Name: Jin Yee</p>",
